        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "ee2b3c6994da0079",
        "text": "Yes, wellspring is not a side project – it is that from which our next book is emerging. It started as an experiment with Ward. We were talking about the challenge of engineering resilient complex systems – they are impossible to fully understand and they randomly fail. That challenge is being faced by many technology companies, such as his. Their code base is so complex that no one person can understand it. Each of its pieces, called microservices, interact in ways that cause unexpected failures. We were comparing that experience to complex human systems, such as what I saw Jami managing as a principal of a school and recognized that there were many similarities. \n"
      },
      "after": "84b7f1b4d9389397",
      "date": 1587678826241
