      "type": "add",
      "id": "e9f3676052979c69",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "e9f3676052979c69",
        "text": "Our experiment was simple: What might happen if, over a three week period, we committed to explore this question of engineering resilient complex systems and pondered it together, me in my wiki, he in his, with us in a learning pod where our wikis were linked into a neighborhood so that we could see how the other was thinking and forming new patterns of meaning. Might his thinking connect with my thinking in ways that opened new creative possibilities for both of us? \n\nWhat we found was that rather than interconnected parallel plans toward the shared goal, ours were disruptive orthogonal planes from which we began to see another emergence from a magical intersection. An experience similar to the emergence experience of my first book, one that I shared in on writing.\n\nWard and I continue to push hard on this exploration, one that integrates the thinking of Whitehead, Piaget, Alexander, Friston, and others where we seek to break free from the constraints of linear thinking and allow the potential of metanoietic consciousness to manifest. \n\nWhat does this have to do with our work with Jami and Jenni? Well, everything. We continually plant these ideas with them and they explore how these new understandings can be used to unleash the creative genius of their students. You see, our generation is of the industrial age, our thinking is Cartesian, linear by nature. But the young, those who are digital natives, are much more comfortable with non-linear thought. The wiki is a platform for non-linear thinking, where space, connection, and patterns allow new meaning to emerge. Magically.\n\nMagically. A word derived from \"magi\", the Zoroastrian priests. An ancient religion that sprang forth from the gardens of Persia, at the center of which was a well, a wellspring, from which the mystery of the unknown emerges to become known. An understanding that now mirrors that of quantum field theory, where emergence manifests through the Higgs field, one defined by dark energy. Mysteriously, where chaos becomes order through consciousness grappling with surprise in a monadic vortex.   "
